# DQ TMaaS AI Coding Standards

## Project Overview
TMaaS (Transformation Management as a Service) marketplace prototype — Next.js 16 App Router, TypeScript strict, Tailwind CSS 4, shadcn/ui, Supabase.

## [SECTION: Favicon / App Icons]

- **Next.js App Router file-based metadata wins.** Put icons in `app/` (`favicon.ico`, `icon.svg`, `apple-icon.png`). Do **not** rely on `metadata.icons` in `app/layout.tsx` alone — `app/favicon.ico` overrides it.
- **Source asset:** `handoff/tmaas/favicon.svg` from `dq_brand_kit` (shared DQ mark). Copy to `app/icon.svg` and `public/favicon.svg`; regenerate PNG sizes (`favicon-16.png` … `favicon-512.png`) and `app/favicon.ico` / `public/favicon.ico` from it when the favicon changes; keep `app/apple-icon.png` (`favicon-180.png`) in sync.
- **Product logos:** `public/brand/tmaas-logo.svg` (light surfaces) and `tmaas-logo-dark.svg` (dark surfaces). Nav uses the product lockup only — **do not** place the DQ monogram beside it (`TMaaSLogo.tsx`). Crop the SVG `viewBox` to the lockup bounds (~`14 22 180 84`) so `<img>` sizing does not reserve empty space beside nav links.
- **Remove stale assets:** delete legacy `app/icon.png` and old favicon files when replacing — browsers request `/favicon.ico` by default and cache aggressively.
- **Verify:** `curl -s http://127.0.0.1:3000/ | grep -i 'rel="icon"'` should list hashed `/favicon.ico`, `/icon.svg`, and `/apple-icon.png` routes.

## [SECTION: Database setup pack]

- **Regenerate:** `npm run db:setup-pack` → `release-1-database-setup/`.
- **Apply on empty DB:** `release-1-database-setup/00_apply_all.sql` or `migrations/01`–`13` in order. Card + PDP copy (09–10) come from `workspace/dba-catalog-copy/` (handoff authority).

## [SECTION: Catalog CSV Guidelines]

- **Source of truth for copy:** `.service-catalog/products.csv` (35 rows) and `.service-catalog/product_variants.csv` (221 rows).
- **Regenerate copy:** `npm run catalog:generate` then `npm run catalog:validate`.
- **Sync static fixture:** `npm run catalog:sync-fixture` — must preserve helper exports (`getServiceById`, `getBestSellers`, etc.) appended after `initialServices`.
- **DB import:** `SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY` + `npm run catalog:import` — upserts products, variants, content, listings.
- **`/supabase/` is gitignored** — migrations and CLI state stay local; do not commit the folder.
- **Variant labels:** Assess, Design, AI Design, Deploy, AI Deploy, Managed (not Implementation / Managed Service).
- **British English** in customer-facing copy fields; `Specialised Operations` title (slug stays `specialized-operations`).
- **Immutable in CSV edits:** id, slug, sku, product_id, collection_id, duration_*, delivery_complexity, implementation_model, timestamps.
- **Standards doc:** `/workspace/catalog-copy-standards.md`

## [SECTION: Contact API Development]

### Contact form API

- The contact form POSTs to `/api/contact` (`api/contact.js` — Vercel serverless on deploy).
- **Local `npm run dev`**: Vite must serve `/api/contact` via `contactApiDevPlugin` in `vite.config.ts`. Do not rely on Vite alone — without the plugin, the route returns 404.
- **Env vars** (in `.env.local`): Graph mail — `MSGRAPH_TENANT_ID`, `MSGRAPH_CLIENT_ID`, `MSGRAPH_CLIENT_SECRET`, `MSGRAPH_SENDER_UPN`, `MSGRAPH_RECIPIENT_EMAIL` (server-only). Turnstile — `VITE_TURNSTILE_SITE_KEY` (client), `TURNSTILE_SECRET_KEY` (server-only). The dev plugin loads server vars with `loadEnv(..., "")`.
- **Abuse controls** (`api/contact-security.js`): per-IP rate limit (5 / 15 min), Cloudflare Turnstile verification (`turnstileToken` in POST body), honeypot field `website` (silent 200 if filled). Validate optional `role` against `MAX_LEN.role` (150).
- **vercel.json**: SPA rewrite must exclude `/api/*` — use `"/((?!api/).*)"` → `/index.html`, not a catch-all `"/(.*)"`.
- Submit errors belong in `submitError` state, not on the `message` field.

### Service-driven contact enquiries

- Service detail CTAs must link with `buildContactPath(service, intent)` (`service`, `type`, `collection`, `intent` query params).
- When `?service=` is present, hide "What are you exploring?" / "What do you need from DQ?" and show the service enquiry summary instead.
- Interest and need are derived in `src/lib/contactFormPrefill.ts` and still submitted to the API.

## [SECTION: Corporate Web Design Standards]

Marketing pages (`/`, `/marketplace`, `/service/:id`) share the **DQ corp web design system** from `DQ_CORPWEB_PROTOTYPE`. They must **not** mirror the corp homepage section stack or copy patterns.

### Copy punctuation
- Do not use em dashes (`—`) in user-facing copy, meta tags, or email templates. Use commas, colons, periods, or a regular hyphen (`-`) instead.

### Share with corp web (design system)
- Body font: **Plus Jakarta Sans** (`font-sans`), not Inter
- Brand colors: `text-dq-navy` (#030F35), `text-dq-orange` (#FB5535)
- Headings: `font-semibold`, not `font-bold`; hero up to `lg:text-8xl`
- Eyebrow labels: `font-mono text-[11px] uppercase tracking-[0.2em] text-dq-orange`
- Section padding: `py-24 px-5 md:px-8 lg:px-10`
- Content max-width: `max-w-[1200px] mx-auto` (heroes may use `max-w-7xl`)
- Alternate backgrounds: `white` / `bg-gray-50`
- Navbar: static `sticky top-0 h-16`, no scroll-morph pill effect
- Cards: `rounded-2xl border border-gray-200 hover:border-dq-orange hover:shadow-xl transition-all duration-300`
- CTAs: `rounded-full`; primary orange on product landing (`bg-dq-orange`); secondary glass (`bg-white/60 backdrop-blur-sm border`)
- Hero backgrounds: `MeshSection` with `hero-grid` overlay and mesh CSS vars from `index.css`
- Footer section labels: `font-mono text-[10px] uppercase tracking-[0.18em] text-gray-400`
- Footer link columns: **Explore** (Marketplace, Talk to our team, flag-gated), **Follow Us** (LinkedIn, X, YouTube, Explore DigitalQatalyst external link). No separate DQ column.
- Footer bottom bar: Privacy and Terms link to in-app `/legal/privacy` and `/legal/terms` when `legal` flag is enabled; otherwise external corp web URLs
- Footer and hero descriptions use `PLATFORM_NAME_EXPANDED` / expanded copy: **Transformation Management as a Service (TMaaS)** via `brandLinks.ts`
- Service count copy is **100+** everywhere (not 50+ or 200+); typical start time is **<1 day** (not 4 wks)
- Corp web links use `https://www.digitalqatalyst.com` base URL; TMaaS product link label is **Marketplace** (not "Design & Deploy Services")
- Platform display name is **Marketplace** (`PLATFORM_NAME`, `PLATFORM_ACRONYM`, and `PLATFORM_BRAND_LINE` in `src/lib/brandLinks.ts`). Do not revert to "Transformation as a Service", "TMaaS", "Transformation Management as a Service", or "Technology Management as a Service" as the platform name.

### Differentiate for product pages (TMaaS landing)
- Use **product landing IA** per `specs/landing-page-prototype-shell.md` v2, default at `/` (`IndexProductLanding`, `src/components/site/landing/v2/`)
- v1 corp-mirror alternate landing at `/landing-v1` (`IndexTraditional`); `/landing-v2` redirects to `/`
- Hero: TMaaS logo, marketplace mockup; orange primary CTA → `/marketplace` (no product badge row)
- Landing navbar: Services nav link stays grey on all routes (no orange active state)
- One dark mesh narrative section (`Why TMaaS`); do not alternate dark sections like corp homepage
- Do **not** add corp-only sections: Team, FAQ, Framework, full ecosystem product grid
- Do **not** copy corp homepage stats, problem copy, or section order verbatim
- Parent brand: optional `Part of DigitalQatalyst` external link; full corp credibility stays on corp web

### Product landing copy (TMaaS positioning)
- **Marketing + SEO first**: plain language, short sentences, searchable terms (`digital transformation`, `marketplace`, `services`, `blueprints`, `AI-powered`)
- Avoid internal jargon on the landing page: `industrialise`, `productised`, `governed fulfilment`, `operating platform`, `architecture-led`
- Hero H1 should include **digital transformation**; subcopy mirrors USP in one or two short sentences (low-cost marketplace, AI-powered blueprints, transparent pricing, weeks not months)
- Problem cards: three short pains (slow, expensive, hard to adapt); closing line ties to marketplace + blueprints
- Outcome cards: cost, speed, scale with substantiated metrics only (`<1 day`, `100+`, `From $1k`)
- Journey steps: Discover (browse) → Evaluate (compare) → Engage (launch with team)
- Primary CTA: **Browse services**; secondary: **Talk to our team**
- Badge row: `TMaaS` + status chip (e.g. Live); page `<title>` and meta description use TMaaS + digital transformation marketplace keywords

### Marketing page copy (Marketplace, Service Detail, Contact)
- Same voice as homepage: plain language, short sentences, SEO terms (`digital transformation`, `marketplace`, `services`, `blueprints`)
- Shared CTA labels: **Browse marketplace** (secondary on landing), **Schedule free advisory** (primary conversion for launch offer in navbar, hero, closing CTA, marketplace launch band); **Talk to our team** remains on footer and service-detail flows; avoid "Explore Marketplace", "Contact Us", "Book a Consultation"
- Launch offer: free transformation advisory via `src/lib/launchOffering.ts` → `/contact?offering=launch-advisory`; marketplace `MarketplaceLaunchOffer` is a single CTA card (ctaOrange mesh + grid, not a service card) below the featured carousel; catalog section uses `pt-10 md:pt-12` below hero
- Landing hero H1: use `landingHeroHeading` from `brandAccent.ts` (corp web scale: `leading-[1.0]`, `sm:text-6xl` through `lg:text-8xl`); two-line split with second line `text-dq-orange`
- Marketplace hero: eyebrow `Digital transformation marketplace`; H1 `Browse transformation services` with **transformation** in `text-dq-orange`; use `landingHeroHeading` scale and tall hero padding (`lg:pb-24 lg:pt-28`, min-height ~360px on desktop)
- Marketplace featured carousel: eyebrow `Curated selection`; H2 `Featured services` (not "Top picks")
- Contact hero: H1 `Tell us what you need. We'll help you get started.`; submit button `Send request`
