## [SECTION: Marketplace Catalog Conventions]

- `useMarketplaceListings` must load the **full catalog once** via `useCatalog()` and apply `filterCatalogServices()` + pagination in memory.
- Do **not** key React Query on filter params or call `fetchCatalogPage()` per filter change — that causes ~3s Supabase round-trips on every checkbox.
- Reserve `fetchCatalogPage` for integration tests or future server-side pagination when the catalog is too large for client filtering.
- Show loading only on the initial catalog fetch (`isLoading && !data`), not when filters change.
- `sortBy: "popular"` must use `sortCatalogByPopularMix()` — stage popularity scores tie across products (all Assess = 100), so a flat sort shows only one type on early pages.
- `fetchCatalogFromSupabase` loads `marketplace_listings_view` then joins variant extras (including `product_content.description` per variant). Never use product-level `short_description` alone for card copy.
- `enrichCatalogListExtras` runs in the background for tags/features/remix/descriptions when placeholder data is shown first.
- `useCatalog` must use `placeholderData: getCatalogPlaceholder` so the grid renders immediately (fixture or sessionStorage cache).
- `CatalogPrefetch` in App warms the catalog on first load.
- `useBestSellers` must derive from `useCatalog()` — never trigger a second full catalog fetch.
- Do not block the marketplace UI with a "Loading catalog" empty state when placeholder data exists.

## [SECTION: PDP Copy Style Guide]

Reference: `/workspace/pdp-copy-style.md`

### Required voice rules

1. **No em dashes** (`—`). Use commas, colons, or full stops instead.
2. **Do not open hero copy with duration** (e.g. never start with "In one week,"). Duration belongs in metadata, timeline, and FAQs.
3. Lead with outcome or scope, not process jargon ("strategic discovery engagement").
4. Name the **solution** (web presence, data platform), not generic "digital presence" unless the product is experience/web.
5. Use **DigitalQatalyst team** (not "DQ advisor").
6. British spelling where already used: organisation, prioritised.

### Buyer-facing labels

- Stage and product display names: `src/lib/marketplaceDisplayLabels.ts` (cards, PDP badges, bundle subtitles). DB `variant_name` slugs stay unchanged.
- Assess: title/card uses **Assess**; PDP type badge uses **Assessment**. Managed customer-facing label is **Managed Service**.
- Transformation Bundle: marketplace card suffix **End-to-end bundle**; PDP H1 suffix **End-to-end transformation**. Flexible set bundles (`Advisory Set`, etc.) use renamed product only (no suffix).
- Bundle PDP subtitle and inclusion line: `BUNDLE_PDP_SUBTITLE`, `BUNDLE_INCLUSION_LINE` in the same module.
- Supabase catalog labels: `npm run db:display-labels:sql` → `supabase/migrations/20250610000013_update_display_labels.sql` (products.title, product_variants, search index).

### Variant SEO copy (required)

- Single source: `src/lib/variantSeoCopy.ts` (hero description, positioning) and `src/lib/serviceFaqsCopy.ts` (FAQs).
- Every variant needs a **unique** hero/description mentioning stage and outcome. Put price and duration in metadata, FAQs, and package card only, not in hero/description body copy.
- Positioning must use correct grammar (`perform` vs `performs` for plural domains). No em dashes.
- Sync fixture: `npm run catalog:sync-variant-copy` before regenerating PDP seed.

### Generator

- PDP seed SQL: `npm run db:pdp-content:sql` → local `supabase/migrations/…` (gitignored; apply via Supabase dashboard or CLI)
- Apply migrations in Supabase SQL Editor after schema extensions are present.
- `fetchPdpContent` must degrade gracefully when PDP tables/columns are not migrated yet.

## [SECTION: React State Naming Patterns]

When destructuring `useState`, the state variable and setter must use matching base names:

```tsx
// Good
const [selectedSectors, setSelectedSectors] = useState<string[]>([]);

// Bad, setter name does not match state; easy to call the wrong function in handlers/reset
const [selectedSectors, setSelectedIndustries] = useState<string[]>([]);
```

When adding reset/clear handlers, verify every setter referenced exists and matches the state it clears.

## [SECTION: SEO MVP Implementation]

### Per-page meta

Use the shared `Seo` component (`react-helmet-async`) on every indexable route. Do not set `document.title` directly.

```tsx
import Seo from "@/components/Seo";
import { HOME_SEO } from "@/lib/seo";

<Seo title={HOME_SEO.title} description={HOME_SEO.description} path={HOME_SEO.path} />
```

- **Brand in titles:** `PLATFORM_ACRONYM` / `SEO_BRAND` = `TMaaS` (not the UI label "Marketplace").
- **Canonical + OG:** `path` must match the route (e.g. `/service/${id}`). Site base URL comes from `VITE_SITE_URL`.
- **Service descriptions:** use `buildServiceMetaDescription()` (title + price + duration + body, max 155 chars).
- **Alternate landings** (`/landing-v1`, `/home`): always `noindex`; keep feature flags off for MVP.

### Structured data (JSON-LD)

Use `JsonLd` + builders in `src/lib/structuredData.ts`:

| Page | Schema |
|------|--------|
| `/` | `Organization` + `WebSite` (+ `SearchAction`) |
| `/contact` | `ContactPage` |
| `/service/:id` | `Service` + `BreadcrumbList` (+ `Offer` when price parses) |

Validate with [Google Rich Results Test](https://search.google.com/test/rich-results) after deploy.

### 404 handling

- **Client:** unknown React Router paths render `NotFound` with `noindex` (not redirect to home).
- **Edge:** `middleware.ts` returns HTTP **404** for paths not in `middleware/allowedRoutes.ts`.
- When enabling a new **public** route via feature flags, add it to `PUBLIC_EXACT_PATHS` in `middleware/allowedRoutes.ts`.

### Static HTML prerender (SSG)

- `postbuild` runs `scripts/prerender-html.ts` — writes route-specific `index.html` files under `dist/` with **title, meta, canonical, OG/Twitter, JSON-LD, and noscript fallback** in the initial HTML (no JS required for crawlers).
- Route payloads live in `src/lib/seoHead.ts` (shared with build script). Keep in sync with page-level `Seo` / `JsonLd` components.
- Paths come from `scripts/seo-routes.ts` (same list as sitemap).
- `PRERENDER_SKIP=true` skips prerender for fast local builds.
- `vercel.json` uses `{ "handle": "filesystem" }` so prerendered files are served before the SPA fallback.

### Build artifacts

- Run `npm run seo:generate` (also runs via `prebuild`) before deploy to refresh `public/sitemap.xml` and `public/robots.txt`.
- Set `VITE_SITE_URL` in production env (no trailing slash).
- Social image: `public/og-image.png` (1200×630).

### New public routes

When adding an indexable page: add `Seo` (+ `JsonLd` if applicable), add URL to `scripts/generate-seo-files.ts` static paths, add to `middleware/allowedRoutes.ts`, regenerate sitemap.

### Post-deploy checks

- Lighthouse SEO score (target 90+) on production URL
- `curl -o /dev/null -s -w "%{http_code}" https://YOUR_DOMAIN/not-a-page` → `404`
